Security review item #1: bearer-token auth on HTTP + WebSocket

- gateway/src/index.ts: load/auto-generate AUTHORCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN in Phase 2c
  (persists to .env, mirrors AUTHORCLAW_VAULT_KEY); AUTHORCLAW_AUTH_DISABLED=1
  escape hatch with a loud startup warning
- Express middleware gates /api/* with a constant-time bearer compare; accepts
  Authorization: Bearer or a ?token= query fallback for native-element GETs
- io.use() gates the Socket.IO handshake (socket.handshake.auth.token)
- "/" now serves the dashboard HTML with the token substituted into a
  __AUTHORCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN__ placeholder; express.static set index:false
- dashboard/dist/index.html: AUTH_TOKEN global + authHeaders()/authUrl();
  api()/apiRaw() send the bearer header; project-file img, download link, and
  TTS Audio URLs carry ?token=
- docs/TODO.md -> docs/COMPLETED.md, STATUS.md, memory entry updated
- Smoke-tested: no token 401, bearer 200, ?token= 200, wrong token 401,
  dashboard loads with placeholder substituted; disabled-mode warning + 200.
  tsc --noEmit clean.

