Security review item #2: tighten CORS

- gateway/src/index.ts: shared corsOptions (one origin callback) applied to
  both Express and the Socket.IO server, driven by AUTHORCLAW_CORS_ORIGINS
  (comma-separated). Unset = deny cross-origin (dashboard is same-origin so
  unaffected); a literal "*" entry = permissive escape hatch, logged loudly.
  Requests with no Origin header (curl/MCP/same-origin) always allowed.
  Startup logs the effective posture.
- tests/smoke-test.sh: default-deny gives no Access-Control-Allow-Origin;
  new Phase 3 starts with an allowlist and asserts listed origin echoed,
  unlisted origin denied. 11 checks total, all pass. tsc --noEmit clean.
- Identified a distinct, stronger control (source-IP allowlist,
  AUTHORCLAW_ALLOWED_IPS) and added it to docs/TODO.md as the next item.

Security review: source-IP allowlist (AUTHORCLAW_ALLOWED_IPS)

- gateway/src/index.ts: network-level allowlist gating ALL clients, in front
  of auth. Express middleware (403 + audit ip_blocked on deny) and a matching
  io.use() handshake gate. ipaddr.js (now a direct dep) handles IPv4/IPv6 +
  IPv4-mapped + CIDR matching; isIpAllowed() treats loopback as always-allowed.
- Unset = allow all + startup notice (enforcement opt-in; auto-deriving a /24
  rejected as a Docker/VPS trap). AUTHORCLAW_TRUST_PROXY=1 reads the client IP
  from X-Forwarded-For for reverse-proxy deploys (off by default, spoofable
  unless behind a sole-ingress proxy). Startup logs the posture.
- package.json: add ipaddr.js ^1.9.1 (was transitive via proxy-addr).
- tests/smoke-test.sh Phase 4 (trust-proxy on): exact IP + CIDR allowed,
  unlisted IP -> 403 even with a valid token (gate precedes auth), loopback
  recovery, enforcement log present. 16 checks total, all pass. tsc clean.
- CLAUDE.md: documented the security-perimeter env vars + the Docker
  source-IP-masking caveat. Corrected the stale "CORS permissive" note.
